  "prompt": "Does IIM Indore select 1 year dropouts for IPM?",
  "response": "The Indian Institute of Management (IIM) Indore offers an Integrated Programme in Management (IPM) that typically requires applicants to meet certain academic criteria. As of the latest information, IIM Indore does not explicitly disqualify applicants who have taken a one-year drop in their education. However, candidates are usually required to have completed their 10th and 12th grades with specified minimum marks to be eligible to apply. \n\nUltimately, the selection process for IPM also involves an entrance exam (IPMAT), and those who qualify are further assessed through written ability tests and personal interviews. IIM Indore focuses on the overall profile of the candidate, so a year drop may be considered if you can justify it well and meet the other criteria and perform well in subsequent rounds.\n\nIt is always a good idea to check the latest official admission guidelines directly from IIM Indore's website or contact their admissions office to get the most accurate and current information.",
